pov you meet some girl from Twitter at a bar

Happy 29th Birthday to my sweet, sweet girl. Every single day I'm happy to celebrate you, but today is even more reason to celebrate. Thank you for coming into my life, loving me & giving me the privilege of loving such a beautiful soul. I love you so 🤍

When I first began thinking of the perfect way to propose to Lindsay, I began with the realization that it should be so intentionally for her that it wouldn’t make sense to anyone else. The animation could be cute to anyone but only Lindsay knew what emotion each scene contained and how it shaped our love. Only she would giggle at the fluffy animated version of our dog. Only she would gasp at the sight of her brother. It could only be her, standing in the living room of the house we bought together watching a barefoot me bare my soul. 

Every single detail was catered to her from the matching clothes to the ring. The first time I met with my jeweler @reedsjewelers to discuss the ring, I told them that I wanted it to be something special that would only be significant to Lindsay. They let me know about hidden details such as birthstones and dates. I immediately knew that I wanted to include her brother’s birthstone and the date she DMd me for the first time. I wanted her ring to be beautiful but have sentiment. When the ring arrived weeks later, I knew it was the one.

Every detail was a whisper to her heart that “I see you for who you are and I love you.”

HUGE THANK YOU to @ardentandelmphoto for these stunning photos and for coming to our home to capture an afternoon we’ll never forget

One thing ab me is I'm gonna eat. Most things you see in this video are substitutes for the regular thing. I eat high volume, low cal, high protein foods to keep me full and maintain healthier eating. 

This was a low cal day, but I don't eat 1600 cals everyday- most days it's more. I don't "cut" or "bulk" so having a rough idea in mind about macros but eating intuitively helps me stay on track for maintenance.

lost files 😮‍💨

Watch me figure out how to squat lol

Form is the most important thing when lifting. Not only will it prevent injuries, but your progress will be quicker when your form is on point. Notice how I lowered the weight significantly when I realized my form felt off. If you're unsure how to do a movement, watching YouTube videos or googling "cues for *insert excersise here*" has always helped me. Filming yourself can also be useful to see how you look. Practice makes perfect.

My fav snack to curve my sweet tooth! 😋
(and to use those old bananas)

RECIPE 👇🏼

Mix together:
1.5 xtra ripe bananas (smashed) 0.5 cup fat free fairlife or protein milk 
0.5 tbsp apple cider vinegar  0.5 tsp vanilla extract
1 cup (120g) self rising flour
0.25 (30g) cup almond flour 
1 scoop vanilla protein powder 
0.25 cup brown sugar truvia substitute 
30g no added sugar chocolate chips (sometimes we add walnuts instead)

Bake at 350 for 40 mins in oiled bread pan

Enjoy 🤭
